The paper deals with learning the optimal topology of Markov networks, which is a problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves graph theory and optimization, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses applications in linear structures, which could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control).
